{{Infobox rugby biography | name = Marcell Coetzee | image = | fullname = Marcell Cornelius Coetzee | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1991|05|08|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Potchefstroom]], [[South Africa]] | height = {{height|m=1.92}} | weight = {{convert|118|kg|stlb lb|0|abbr=on}}<ref>https://www.ulsterrugby.com/team/senior-team</ref> | nickname = | occupation = | school = [[Port Natal High School]] | university = | relatives = | position = [[Flanker (rugby union)|Flanker]] | currentclub = [[Ulster Rugby|Ulster]] | youthyears1 = 2010–2011 | youthclubs1 = {{Rut Sharks (Currie Cup)}} | years1 = 2011–2013 | clubs1 = {{Rut Sharks XV}} | apps1 = 8 | points1 = 15 | years2 = 2011–2013 | clubs2 = {{Rut Sharks (Currie Cup)|CC=y}} | apps2 = 24 | points2 = 5 | years3 = 2011–2016 | clubs3 = {{Rut Sharks}} | apps3 = 74 | points3 = 70 | years4 = 2015–2016 | clubs4 = [[Honda Heat]] | apps4 = 9 | points4 = 15 | years5 = 2017–present | clubs5 = [[Ulster Rugby|Ulster]] | apps5 = 6 | points5 = 0 | repyears1 = 2012–present | repteam1 = {{nrut|South Africa}} | repcaps1 = 28 | reppoints1 = 30 | repyears2 = 2015 | repteam2 = Springbok XV | repcaps2 = 1 | reppoints2 = 0 | clubupdate = 1 September 2018 | repupdate = 8 August 2015 }}
'''Marcell Cornelius Coetzee''' (born 8 May 1991) is a [[South Africa]]n [[rugby football|rugby]] union player who currently plays for [[Ulster Rugby|Ulster]] in the [[Pro14]]. He plays as a [[Flanker (rugby union)|flanker]].
==South Africa== Coetzee made his debut in [[Super Rugby]] for the [[Sharks (rugby union)|Sharks]] against the [[Brumbies (rugby)|Brumbies]] on Saturday 7 May 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=Marcell Coetzee included in Sharks 22|url=http://www.sharksacademy.co.za/News_05052011.html|publisher=The Sharks Academy|accessdate=26 July 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120729052314/http://www.sharksacademy.co.za/News_05052011.html|archivedate=29 July 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He has offloading skills that have been likened to those of [[Sonny Bill Williams]].<ref>http://www.theaustralian.com.au/sport/opinion/system-mirrors-our-place-behind-south-africa-and-new-zealand/story-e6frg7po-1226431197524</ref>
[[Heyneke Meyer]], [[Springbok]] coach, included him in the national squad to face [[England]] in a test series where Coetzee made his Springbok test debut on 9 June 2012 in [[Durban]].<ref>http://www.springboksupporter.co.za/SARU/Player-Profiles/Marcell-Coetzee.aspx</ref>
==Abroad== Coetzee joined [[Japan]]ese [[Top League]] side [[Honda Heat]] for the 2015–2016 season.<ref name="新加入選手のお知らせ">{{cite press release | url=http://www.honda-heat.jp/topics/2015/20150622/sinmenba-.html | title=新加入選手のお知らせ | publisher=Honda Heat | date=22 June 2015 | accessdate=22 June 2015 | language=Japanese}}</ref>
In February 2016, it was announced that he would join Irish [[Pro14|Pro12]] side [[Ulster Rugby|Ulster]] on a three-year deal starting in the 2016–2017 season.<ref name="Marcell Coetzee signing confirmed">{{cite press release | url=http://www.ulsterrugby.com/news/14580.php | title=Marcell Coetzee signing confirmed | publisher=Ulster Rugby | date=11 February 2016 | accessdate=11 February 2016}}</ref> Coetzee featured sparingly in his first two seasons with Ulster, due to recurring knee injury problems.<ref>Ulster flanker Marcell Coetzee ruled out for nine months, BBC Sport, 13 October 2017.</ref>
